  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Children with chronic otitis media have more resistant bacteria that require surgical
      intervention to eradicate the infections. The study will evaluate the dominant bacteria and
      their sensitivities to antibiotics. The information will assist in better treatment plans for
      children with chronic infections.

      The data will also assess the changing patterns in the bacteria colonizing middle ear fluid.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
